  "@id": "ocp:sep/legal-interpretation",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Legal Interpretation",
    "description": "Legal interpretation involves scrutinizing legal texts such as the texts of statutes, constitutions, contracts, and wills. This chapter introduces the foundational question of what legal interpretation, by its nature, seeks - and competing answers to that question. It goes on to canvas leading substantive theories of legal interpretation and examines in greater depth a few influential theories and difficulties they encounter. Finally, the chapter considers how theories of legal interpretation should be defended and evaluated.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-22T05:30:19.102Z",
